==English==

===Etymology===
{{L.}} ''[[prospectus]]'', from ''[[prospicere]], [[prospectum]]'', to look forward; [[pro]] before, forward + ''[[specere]], [[spicere]]'', look, to see.

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# The [[potential]] things that may come to pass, usually favorable.

===Verb===
{{en-infl-reg-consonant|prospect||}}

# To search, as for [[gold]]; one who surveys the land for favorable prospects.

